7. Conclusion
This project successfully realizes the handwritten digit recognition system based on Raspberry Pi, which integrates the functions of image acquisition, preprocessing, model training, hardware control and result display. The team overcame the problem of limited hardware resources and optimized the division of labor to achieve efficient collaboration. The comparison experiment shows that the CNN model has higher recognition accuracy than the KNN model. In the process of project development, we not only acquired rich technical skills, but also formed a deeper understanding of computer professional learning. At the same time, we put forward targeted optimization suggestions for the hardware problems of Raspberry Pi encountered in the project, which provides a reference for subsequent similar projects. This project is an important practice for us to combine theory with practice, and lays a solid foundation for our future study and work in the field of computer science.


